Interface MultipleHistoryReferencesContainer

    public interface MultipleHistoryReferencesContainer

    • Method Detail

      • getHistoryReference

        HistoryReference getHistoryReference()
        Returns the HistoryReference of the contained message. Might be null if no message is present.

        If multiple messages are present the HistoryReference of the first one is returned.

        Specified by:
        getHistoryReference in interface SingleHistoryReferenceContainer
        Returns:
        the HistoryReference of the contained message or null if no message is present.
        See Also:
        HistoryReference

      • getHistoryReferences

        List<HistoryReference> getHistoryReferences()
        Returns all the HistoryReferences of the selected messages.

        No assumptions should be made on the actual implementation type of the List returned by this method (for example, it might be unmodifiable or its elements lazy loaded).

        Returns:
        a List with all the HistoryReferences of the selected messages, never null.
        See Also:
        MultipleMessagesContainer.getNumberOfMessages()
